1
00:00:07,291 --> 00:00:09,500
["Such Great Heights"
by Iron &amp; Wine playing]

2
00:00:17,208 --> 00:00:24,208
OTARU GENERAL HOSPITAL

3
00:00:28,166 --> 00:00:34,416
♪ I am thinking it's a sign ♪

4
00:00:34,916 --> 00:00:39,000
♪ That the freckles in our eyes ♪

5
00:00:39,083 --> 00:00:42,666
♪ Are mirror images ♪

6
00:00:42,750 --> 00:00:46,500
♪ And when we kiss they're perfectly… ♪

7
00:00:46,583 --> 00:00:47,416
Kazu.

8
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:50,291
♪ I… ♪

9
00:00:51,125 --> 00:00:53,291
There's fireworks through the window.

10
00:00:53,375 --> 00:00:54,250
[Kazu] Really?

11
00:00:56,291 --> 00:00:57,583
-There.
-Wow.

12
00:00:58,625 --> 00:01:00,666
-Oh, yeah.
-[laughs]

13
00:01:00,750 --> 00:01:03,666
-Those are kinda outta nowhere.
-Mm. They are, aren't they?

14
00:01:04,250 --> 00:01:07,250
They're far away and… kinda little.

15
00:01:07,958 --> 00:01:10,250
I wonder where they're coming from?

16
00:01:12,125 --> 00:01:15,250
-Could be Mt. Misato?
-Oh yeah. Could be.

17
00:01:16,333 --> 00:01:17,833
I just love fireworks.

18
00:01:18,333 --> 00:01:19,916
They're pretty, aren't they?

19
00:01:21,125 --> 00:01:24,000
Maybe people are celebrating
something good that happened?

20
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:25,375
Maybe they are.

21
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:28,375
That's gotta be what's going on, right?

22
00:01:28,458 --> 00:01:29,916
Way to go!

23
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,666
[both laugh]

24
00:01:31,750 --> 00:01:35,083
I wanna see the summer fireworks again
with you, okay?

25
00:01:35,166 --> 00:01:37,166
[music fades]

26
00:01:39,375 --> 00:01:40,416
Oh, yeah.

27
00:01:46,083 --> 00:01:47,083
I'm sorry.

28
00:01:48,791 --> 00:01:50,875
All right, what are you apologizing for?

29
00:01:54,583 --> 00:01:56,041
I don't think I'll make it

30
00:01:57,375 --> 00:01:58,833
to the summer fireworks.

31
00:02:02,083 --> 00:02:03,041
I know I won't.

32
00:02:07,208 --> 00:02:08,375
Well, I think you will.

33
00:02:08,916 --> 00:02:10,416
I just know you will.

34
00:02:11,125 --> 00:02:12,208
You'll live.

35
00:02:12,291 --> 00:02:15,166
And you'll see the fireworks with me.

36
00:02:17,625 --> 00:02:18,666
[chuckles]

37
00:02:20,541 --> 00:02:22,458
All right then, I guess I will.

38
00:02:22,541 --> 00:02:24,125
Mm-hmm. You're going.

39
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,125
And now, guess what. I brought you apples.

40
00:02:27,208 --> 00:02:28,916
Want one? I'm gonna have one too.

41
00:02:29,416 --> 00:02:31,708
No, uh, not right now.

42
00:02:32,375 --> 00:02:33,250
[woman] Hmm?

43
00:02:35,791 --> 00:02:38,375
You know what? I will, uh, have one.

44
00:02:38,458 --> 00:02:40,416
I was just thinking
an apple would be good.

45
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:41,833
-So thanks.
-[giggles]

46
00:02:41,916 --> 00:02:43,833
Yes, I win.

47
00:02:43,916 --> 00:02:45,208
[chuckles]

48
00:02:45,291 --> 00:02:47,833
So what should we do when you're all well?

49
00:02:47,916 --> 00:02:48,791
Here.

50
00:02:50,083 --> 00:02:51,875
Mm…

51
00:02:51,958 --> 00:02:53,958
[tender piano music playing]

52
00:02:54,875 --> 00:02:55,958
Scuba dive,

53
00:02:57,083 --> 00:02:59,375
skydive, or, uh, bungee jumping.

54
00:02:59,458 --> 00:03:02,000
Mm, kinda rough on your heart, isn't it?

55
00:03:02,083 --> 00:03:04,083
[both laugh]

56
00:03:05,291 --> 00:03:08,125
I was hoping you'd say
we'd go on a trip together.

57
00:03:09,291 --> 00:03:10,250
Oh yeah.

58
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,541
And where should we go together?

59
00:03:13,625 --> 00:03:14,833
Mm,

60
00:03:15,666 --> 00:03:18,250
someplace nice and warm, maybe.

61
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:20,541
Mm, sounds good.

62
00:03:20,625 --> 00:03:21,541
Mm-hmm.

63
00:03:23,083 --> 00:03:25,000
Mmm! These are great.

64
00:03:25,083 --> 00:03:27,458
Yeah, right? I got the best ones for you.

65
00:03:27,541 --> 00:03:29,666
The former Miss Apple
knows her stuff, huh?

66
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:30,875
[woman chuckles]

67
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:32,833
-Mm!
-Mm.

68
00:03:32,916 --> 00:03:35,291
-Oh!
-[laughs]

69
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:53,750
[sighs]

70
00:03:54,458 --> 00:03:55,458
[sniffles]

71
00:03:58,875 --> 00:03:59,875
[sighs]

72
00:04:01,583 --> 00:04:02,708
[sobs]

73
00:04:16,625 --> 00:04:19,000
[breathes deeply]

74
00:04:22,833 --> 00:04:23,791
[sniffles]

75
00:04:28,708 --> 00:04:30,708
[helicopter engine roars overhead]

76
00:04:57,666 --> 00:04:58,500
MISS APPLE

77
00:04:58,583 --> 00:05:01,125
[woman 1] Ah, it smells so good. Yummy.

78
00:05:01,791 --> 00:05:03,041
I'm back!

79
00:05:03,125 --> 00:05:05,125
-[man 1] There's my girl.
-[woman 2] Hi, sweetie!

80
00:05:05,708 --> 00:05:07,291
[boy] Hey, how do I solve this?

81
00:05:08,083 --> 00:05:10,541
And how is Kazumasa doing, hmm?

82
00:05:11,208 --> 00:05:13,041
So handsome. Cute, as always.

83
00:05:13,125 --> 00:05:14,833
Strange answer, but okay.

84
00:05:14,916 --> 00:05:18,083
[woman 1] Really?
Well, I'm glad to hear it. It's so sweet.

85
00:05:18,166 --> 00:05:20,916
Yeah. Ah, he's so good-looking.

86
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,291
[laughter]

87
00:05:22,375 --> 00:05:23,708
When's Uncle Kazumasa coming home?

88
00:05:23,791 --> 00:05:26,458
Mm, we're not sure. Why?

89
00:05:26,541 --> 00:05:28,708
Because he is the best tutor there is.

90
00:05:28,791 --> 00:05:32,625
Other than him, no one else in this house
is able to tutor me better.

91
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:34,041
What?

92
00:05:34,916 --> 00:05:37,791
Oh man, did you hear?
We're a bunch of idiots.

93
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:40,166
[man 2] I'm sorry
that we're all too stupid.

94
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:43,333
I'll tell him that if he's not out soon,

95
00:05:43,416 --> 00:05:45,375
your brain just might turn to jelly.

96
00:05:45,458 --> 00:05:46,750
-Thank you!
-[man 2] That's right.

97
00:05:46,833 --> 00:05:48,250
You should beg for his help.

98
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:49,916
[woman 2] Oh, I'm so sorry.

99
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:52,000
[woman 1] No, it's okay. It's our fault.

100
00:05:52,083 --> 00:05:52,916
[laughs]

101
00:06:03,291 --> 00:06:04,875
The color's really good this year.

102
00:06:04,958 --> 00:06:06,916
-[man 1] Yeah, good thing, huh?
-Mm-hmm.

103
00:06:09,375 --> 00:06:10,708
[phone ringing]

104
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:14,791
[gasps]

105
00:06:17,458 --> 00:06:19,000
Yes, this is her.

106
00:06:37,291 --> 00:06:39,291
[footsteps rapidly approaching]

107
00:06:46,791 --> 00:06:48,416
[panting]

108
00:06:50,291 --> 00:06:51,333
Mm-hmm.

109
00:06:58,166 --> 00:06:59,333
You can do this.

110
00:07:00,583 --> 00:07:03,708
God is telling you… to live.

111
00:07:06,333 --> 00:07:08,333
[ethereal music playing]

112
00:07:16,375 --> 00:07:17,333
[sighs]

113
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:19,833
[tender piano music playing]

114
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,083
[inhales]

115
00:07:28,833 --> 00:07:29,875
[exhales]

116
00:07:34,833 --> 00:07:35,666
Mm.

117
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:37,750
[monitors beeping]

118
00:07:53,166 --> 00:07:55,500
-[coordinator] It's here.
-[surgeon] Let's start trimming.

119
00:07:55,583 --> 00:07:57,416
-[assistant] Yes, sir.
-[surgeon] Ischemic time?

120
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:59,750
-[coordinator] One hour and forty minutes.
-[surgeon] Okay.

121
00:08:03,583 --> 00:08:05,583
[tender piano music continues]

122
00:08:11,333 --> 00:08:13,083
[ethereal music playing]

123
00:08:13,166 --> 00:08:14,000
Kazu. [echoes]

124
00:08:16,708 --> 00:08:17,916
[waves crashing]

125
00:08:18,666 --> 00:08:20,708
[reverse-sounding piano playing]

126
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:22,791
[ethereal music continues]

127
00:08:24,041 --> 00:08:25,541
[rescuers] Can you hear me?

128
00:08:30,458 --> 00:08:32,125
[music fades]

129
00:08:50,291 --> 00:08:51,166
[woman] Kazu?

130
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:02,583
Kazu.

131
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:14,500
[emotional music playing]

132
00:09:17,375 --> 00:09:18,291
Hello…

133
00:09:23,791 --> 00:09:24,666
again.

134
00:09:25,583 --> 00:09:26,583
[sobs]

135
00:09:46,375 --> 00:09:48,375
[emotional music continues]

136
00:09:49,666 --> 00:09:50,916
[woman] Everything okay?

137
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,916
[Kazu] Fine, thanks.

138
00:09:55,291 --> 00:09:58,083
I feel comfortable. My body feels good.

139
00:09:58,166 --> 00:09:59,458
I feel much lighter.

140
00:10:00,708 --> 00:10:01,625
[woman] I see.

141
00:10:27,166 --> 00:10:28,083
[Kazu] Ah…

142
00:10:36,750 --> 00:10:38,750
[emotional music continues]

143
00:10:43,416 --> 00:10:44,666
[man 1] They're back. Hey, Dad!

144
00:10:44,750 --> 00:10:46,250
[man 2] Huh? Oh!

145
00:10:47,125 --> 00:10:48,541
Hey!

146
00:10:49,416 --> 00:10:50,416
Oh!

147
00:10:56,708 --> 00:10:58,416
-[Kazu] I'm back!
-[man 1] Welcome home!

148
00:10:58,500 --> 00:10:59,500
[man 2] Welcome home!

149
00:10:59,583 --> 00:11:01,291
-Uncle Kazumasa!
-Hey, Yuma! [laughs]

150
00:11:01,375 --> 00:11:03,208
-Wow, you got taller, didn't you?
-Yeah, I did.

151
00:11:03,291 --> 00:11:04,833
-Welcome home!
-[Kazu] Right?

152
00:11:05,416 --> 00:11:08,291
I'm sorry I made you guys
worry about me for so long.

153
00:11:08,375 --> 00:11:09,208
[woman 1 laughs]

154
00:11:09,291 --> 00:11:10,875
-[Yuma] Let's go!
-[woman 1] Come on in.

155
00:11:10,958 --> 00:11:12,208
-[Kazu] Okay, yeah.
-[woman 2] Come in!

156
00:11:12,291 --> 00:11:13,458
-[Kazu] My bags.
-[man 2] I'll get 'em!

157
00:11:13,541 --> 00:11:15,458
-Tomo, help me out?
-[man 1] Just give them to me.

158
00:11:15,541 --> 00:11:17,291
-Dad, are you sure?
-Here. Oh, it's fine.

159
00:11:17,375 --> 00:11:18,625
-This is heavy.
-What is in here?

160
00:11:18,708 --> 00:11:20,041
-You are old!
-Hey, you take this.

161
00:11:20,125 --> 00:11:22,000
-[Yuma] I'll do it!
-[Tomo] Are you sure?

162
00:11:22,083 --> 00:11:23,041
[Yuma] It's okay.

163
00:11:23,125 --> 00:11:24,625
-Be careful.
-[man 2] Give me a second.

164
00:11:24,708 --> 00:11:26,208
[woman 1] Hurry, the food's coming.

165
00:11:26,291 --> 00:11:28,250
-Ta-da!
-Wow! This all looks so good!

166
00:11:28,333 --> 00:11:29,541
Let me get this out of the way.

167
00:11:29,625 --> 00:11:31,333
[woman 2] Okay, guys!
It's ready! Let's eat!

168
00:11:31,416 --> 00:11:33,291
All right, everyone tell me
what you wanna drink.

169
00:11:33,375 --> 00:11:34,250
Who here wants coffee?

170
00:11:34,333 --> 00:11:35,250
-Me.
-[man 2] Oh, I do.

171
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:36,250
-I do.
-Here.

172
00:11:37,083 --> 00:11:39,333
[man 2] What?
I thought you didn't like coffee.

173
00:11:40,750 --> 00:11:42,375
That's… right. Yeah.

174
00:11:42,916 --> 00:11:45,125
I don't know. [chuckles]
I just felt like having a little.

175
00:11:45,208 --> 00:11:46,708
What did the doctor say?

176
00:11:46,791 --> 00:11:50,125
I… I guess it's okay.
All they said was not to have any alcohol.

177
00:11:50,208 --> 00:11:52,333
-I want coffee too! I'll have some!
-Here.

178
00:11:52,416 --> 00:11:54,083
-[woman 1] What?
-[man 2] Now he wants some.

179
00:11:54,166 --> 00:11:56,458
-Might wanna wait till you're older.
-[Yuma] I wanna try it.

180
00:11:56,541 --> 00:11:58,083
[woman 3] Okay, I'll pour you some.

181
00:12:00,791 --> 00:12:02,333
-Ew!
-[all laugh]

182
00:12:02,416 --> 00:12:04,250
-See, we told you.
-I knew you wouldn't like it.

183
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:06,500
All right, Yuma. Here.
I got some juice for you.

184
00:12:06,583 --> 00:12:08,416
-[Yuma] Yay!
-Yeah, you'll like this better.

185
00:12:08,916 --> 00:12:10,500
[woman 3] Coffee is kinda bitter, huh?

186
00:12:10,583 --> 00:12:12,833
-[man 2 laughs]
-[woman 3 laughs]

187
00:12:17,208 --> 00:12:18,500
I like this.

188
00:12:18,583 --> 00:12:19,708
[all exclaim]

189
00:12:19,791 --> 00:12:21,000
[Kazu] It's really good.

190
00:12:21,083 --> 00:12:22,958
-[chuckles] Yeah?
-[Kazu laughs] Yeah.

191
00:12:55,541 --> 00:12:56,541
[Kazu sighs]

192
00:12:56,625 --> 00:12:58,916
You okay? Are you tired?

193
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:01,208
-No. I'm okay, thanks.
-[chuckles]

194
00:13:04,125 --> 00:13:05,375
I feel so good

195
00:13:06,458 --> 00:13:09,333
that I'm surprised at myself.

196
00:13:11,958 --> 00:13:12,791
But

197
00:13:13,833 --> 00:13:15,791
it does feel a little strange.

198
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:22,250
It almost feels like my body
hasn't really accepted this heart yet.

199
00:13:24,041 --> 00:13:26,625
Or, actually, it's like the opposite.

200
00:13:27,458 --> 00:13:29,583
This heart hasn't accepted my body.

201
00:13:30,666 --> 00:13:33,541
It's as if there's someone here with me.

202
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:36,875
It really is a strange feeling.

203
00:13:36,958 --> 00:13:39,916
Mm. Yeah, that is strange.

204
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:40,958
[Kazu] Mm.

205
00:13:41,791 --> 00:13:46,083
But I can't believe how great I feel.
Like… I can do anything.

206
00:13:46,166 --> 00:13:47,375
[laughs]

207
00:13:48,208 --> 00:13:49,916
-That's good to hear.
-Mm.

208
00:13:50,583 --> 00:13:51,458
Mm-hmm.

209
00:13:53,875 --> 00:13:56,041
Thank you for everything.

210
00:13:56,125 --> 00:13:57,208
[woman] Mm-hmm.

211
00:14:07,416 --> 00:14:11,500
As soon as the doctor says okay,
I can start working again.

212
00:14:12,125 --> 00:14:13,083
Mm-hmm.

213
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,375
It's great, isn't it?

214
00:14:15,458 --> 00:14:17,875
I'm glad you took sick leave
instead of quitting.

215
00:14:18,833 --> 00:14:19,833
So optimistic.

216
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:21,166
Mm-hmm.

217
00:14:22,875 --> 00:14:23,791
I wanna thank you.

218
00:14:23,875 --> 00:14:25,250
[both laugh]

219
00:14:26,666 --> 00:14:28,291
-And I thought before that…
-Hmm?

220
00:14:28,375 --> 00:14:30,166
-…let's go somewhere. All right?
-[gasps]

221
00:14:30,250 --> 00:14:31,375
Yeah! Yay!

222
00:14:31,458 --> 00:14:32,583
[both laugh]

223
00:14:33,541 --> 00:14:34,625
[woman moans happily]

224
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:36,458
I also thought…

225
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:39,666
that we, uh,

226
00:14:40,541 --> 00:14:42,041
could have a few kids one day.

227
00:14:47,708 --> 00:14:49,416
[breathes deeply]

228
00:14:53,208 --> 00:14:55,208
[indistinct chattering]

229
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:11,250
-[woman] It's really busy here.
-Mm.

230
00:15:20,416 --> 00:15:22,083
I'm gonna go in here a second.

231
00:15:22,166 --> 00:15:23,833
[Kazu] Okay. I'll wait upstairs.

232
00:15:23,916 --> 00:15:24,875
Mm-hmm.

233
00:15:41,833 --> 00:15:43,833
[airplane engine roaring]

234
00:15:47,291 --> 00:15:49,166
[child 1] Tag! [giggles]

235
00:16:43,625 --> 00:16:44,916
[note plays]

236
00:16:46,583 --> 00:16:48,583
[poignant piano music playing]

237
00:17:53,250 --> 00:17:55,250
[music fades]

238
00:18:02,791 --> 00:18:04,958
["I Want You Back"
by The Jackson 5 playing]

239
00:18:26,208 --> 00:18:27,416
[man 1] This guy's good.

240
00:18:34,333 --> 00:18:35,291
Beautiful.

241
00:19:24,375 --> 00:19:26,625
-[music ends]
-[crowd cheering]

242
00:19:31,083 --> 00:19:32,208
[exhales sharply]

243
00:20:08,250 --> 00:20:09,583
That was amazing.

244
00:20:10,208 --> 00:20:11,166
You play the piano?

245
00:20:22,791 --> 00:20:23,625
Kazu.

246
00:20:25,166 --> 00:20:27,166
Let's go. Okay?

247
00:20:27,250 --> 00:20:28,166
Let's go.

248
00:20:31,458 --> 00:20:32,958
-Mm.
-[woman chuckles]

249
00:20:39,666 --> 00:20:41,916
[panting]

250
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:57,375
[breathing heavily]

251
00:21:10,333 --> 00:21:12,458
["Beauty All Around" by Hush Kids playing]

252
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,041
Are you nervous?

253
00:21:28,791 --> 00:21:29,875
It's been a while.

254
00:21:30,541 --> 00:21:32,333
[chuckles softly] Yes, it has.

255
00:21:32,416 --> 00:21:33,250
Mm.

256
00:21:34,041 --> 00:21:36,583
♪ With a hundred million flowers ♪

257
00:21:36,666 --> 00:21:38,250
♪ I'm looking for a clock… ♪

258
00:21:38,333 --> 00:21:39,750
Don't worry. You'll be fine.

259
00:21:39,833 --> 00:21:42,166
♪ That doesn't count the hours… ♪

260
00:21:42,250 --> 00:21:43,083
Hmm.

261
00:21:45,916 --> 00:21:48,041
NISEKO STATION

262
00:21:48,125 --> 00:21:49,458
-[Kazu] Thanks.
-[woman] Okay.

263
00:21:49,541 --> 00:21:51,583
-[Kazu] Here I go.
-[woman] Okay, good luck!

264
00:21:51,666 --> 00:21:54,125
Take breaks, okay? Call when you're done.

